      </relatedmaterial>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_3ef11f8bb2d96e9990414eb224503f56">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Katherine Dunham collection consists of five separate acquisitions of material created and used by Katherine Dunham, documenting her career as a choreographer, dancer, and anthropologist. Included are correspondence between Dunham and her friend and assistant, Dorothy Gray, photographs of Dunham and other dancers, financial agreements, correspondence mostly about Dunham's touring schedule, a Langston Hughes autograph, canceled checks, a sketchbook with Dunham's diary entries from her 1958 residency in Tokyo, and programs, broadsides, headshots, promotional material, playbills, postcards, and performance photographs. Also included is an invitation and map to Habitation Leclerc, a resort owned by Katherine Dunham in Port-au-Prince, Haiti.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <userestrict id="aspace_753d91d03cdbeca0873c847071525b0c">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>The Katherine Dunham collection is the physical property of the Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library, Yale University. Literary rights, including copyright, belong to the authors or their legal heirs and assigns. For further information, consult the appropriate curator.</p>
      </userestrict>
